webpackJsonp([0xe1004634b226],{522:function(a,t){a.exports={data:{wordpressWpLessons:{id:"aee2b3f5-1c70-5add-a7e6-52814584e936",wordpress_id:5968,title:"GIMP: Creating Animations",slug:"gimp-creating-animations",content:'<h2>Overview and Goals</h2>\n<p>When you understand the basics of GIMP, it’s very easy to transition to intermediate skills such as using <b>Layers</b>. Layers can be used to create animations, also known as gifs. Layers are commonly used in image editing and retouching software other than GIMP, such as Adobe Photoshop, so it’s useful to get into the habit of using them.</p>\n<h2>Using Layers in GIMP</h2>\n<h3>Opening the Layers Toolbox</h3>\n<p>After you have created your workspace, in the GIMP toolbar, locate Windows and then navigate to <b>Dockable Dialogs</b>. Click <b>Layers</b>. You may also use the shortcut Command + L.</p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/open_layers.png"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-5970" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/open_layers-1024x662.png" alt="" width="625" height="404" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/open_layers-1024x662.png 1024w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/open_layers-300x194.png 300w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/open_layers-768x497.png 768w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/open_layers-155x100.png 155w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/open_layers-624x404.png 624w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/open_layers-100x65.png 100w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/open_layers-750x485.png 750w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/open_layers.png 1192w" sizes="(max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/layers_toolbox.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-5971" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/layers_toolbox-191x300.png" alt="" width="191" height="300" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/layers_toolbox-191x300.png 191w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/layers_toolbox-64x100.png 64w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/layers_toolbox.png 211w" sizes="(max-width: 191px) 100vw, 191px" /></a></p>\n<h3>Creating or Duplicating Layers</h3>\n<p>Once you have created your first frame in the workplane, you will probably want to duplicate it and change it slightly in your second frame. In order to duplicate your frame, you will select the Duplicate Layer icon in the Layers toolbox, shown below. Keep frames in the order they will appear by clicking twice on the title of the layer to rename them accordingly. If you would like to create a new layer and not duplicate an existing one, the Create Layer icon is on the bottom left of the Layers toolbox.</p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/duplicate_layer.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-5972" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/duplicate_layer-185x300.png" alt="" width="185" height="300" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/duplicate_layer-185x300.png 185w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/duplicate_layer-62x100.png 62w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/duplicate_layer.png 197w" sizes="(max-width: 185px) 100vw, 185px" /></a></p>\n<h3>Saving Your Animation</h3>\n<p>When you have created all your frames, save your animation by selecting <b>Export As</b> from the GIMP toolbar. Give your animation a title and change the file type from .PNG to <b>.GIF</b>. GIMP recognizes this file type as an animation and a window will appear prompting you to save your project <b>As animation</b> &#8211; be sure to select this box. Change Frame disposal where unspecified to <b>One frame per layer (replace)</b>. You may also choose to change the delay between frames to be slower or faster. To play your animation, drag the file from your desktop to a web browser.</p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_1.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-5973" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_1-141x300.png" alt="" width="141" height="300" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_1-141x300.png 141w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_1-47x100.png 47w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_1.png 203w" sizes="(max-width: 141px) 100vw, 141px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_2.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-5974" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_2-300x40.png" alt="" width="300" height="40" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_2-300x40.png 300w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_2-768x103.png 768w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_2-200x27.png 200w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_2-624x84.png 624w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_2-100x13.png 100w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_2-750x101.png 750w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/saving_gif_2.png 879w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/save_gif_3.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-5975" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/save_gif_3-300x271.png" alt="" width="300" height="271" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/save_gif_3-300x271.png 300w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/save_gif_3-111x100.png 111w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/save_gif_3-100x90.png 100w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/save_gif_3.png 418w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a></p>\n'}},pathContext:{}}}});
